# 2. Test with a Simple Java Program (Same Driver as Spring)

If the Spring app uses the **IBM Toolbox JDBC driver (`jt400.jar`)**, replicate the exact driver behavior.

Example minimal program:

```java
import java.sql.*;

public class TestAS400 {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        String url = "jdbc:as400://HOSTNAME";
        String user = "USER";
        String password = "PASSWORD";

        Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection(url, user, password);

        System.out.println("Connected!");

        Statement stmt = conn.createStatement();
        ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery(
            "SELECT * FROM QSYS2.SYSTABLES FETCH FIRST 1 ROW ONLY"
        );

        while(rs.next()){
            System.out.println("Success reading table");
        }

        conn.close();
    }
}
```

Run it on **macOS** with the same driver used by WebSphere.

If this fails while VDI works → the issue is **environmental**.

