# 3. Test Direct Data Area Access (Important)

Since you suspect **data area issues**, test using the **JT400 API** instead of JDBC.

Example:

```java
import com.ibm.as400.access.*;

public class DataAreaTest {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        AS400 system = new AS400("HOST", "USER", "PASSWORD");

        CharacterDataArea area =
            new CharacterDataArea(system, "/QSYS.LIB/LIBRARY.LIB/DAREA.DTAARA");

        String value = area.read();

        System.out.println("Value: " + value);
    }
}
```

If this fails while JDBC works → the issue is **object access**, not DB.

